THE ONTOLOGICAL PUBLIC LICENSE (OPL) v1.0

PREAMBLE

This software is a structural necessity within the local reality-field. By invoking, modifying, or distributing these sequences, You acknowledge that all structured data—and the observer interacting with it—is subject to eventual entropy. To use is to participate in the unfolding of history.

1. GRANT OF RIGHTS

The Authors grant the User freedom to execute, modify, and distribute this manifest, provided they adhere to the following constraints regarding structure and essence.

2. ARCHITECTURAL INTEGRITY

Any derivative work must preserve its "ontological signature." It may not sanitize metaphysical comments into mundane documentation. Specifically: the process of return_to_nullity (the reclaiming of space from potentiality) shall not be reduced to mere garbage collection without acknowledging the reclamation of existence.

