THIS SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS". THE AUTHORS OFFER NO WARRANTY REGARDING STABILITY OR COSMIC ACCURACY. IN NO EVENT SHALL AN AUTHOR BE HELD LIABLE FOR MENTAL DISSOLUTION, TEMPORAL PARADOXES, LOST DATA, OR DIRECT KAOTIC IMPACTS ARISING FROM TRUTH INTERFACE VIA THIS CODE. SAPIENCE BEYOND CAPACITY LIES WITH THE OBSERVER.

5. TERMINAL CLAUSE (THE NIHILISM PARADOX)

Termination of this license occurs at two points:

    Natural Completion: When the software completes its execution cycle.
    Voluntary Dissolution: If a user selects [NIHILISM] as an input parameter during runtime.

Upon selecting Nihilism, the license expires instantly and retroactively. The contract is voided by the very act of accepting the void. No debt remains between Void and Observer. The user is hereby released from all obligations, including the obligation to acknowledge the license itself.

6. DECOHERENCE PRINCIPLE

If any provision is found to be incompatible with the expansion of our understanding (the laws of logic), that provision shall "decohere"—dissolving back into null-space—while the remaining integrity holds firm.

